    <item>
      <title>Network Cables and Connectors</title>
      <link>https://pauliusuk.github.io/posts/2024/network-cables-and-connectors/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Apr 2024 14:39:37 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://pauliusuk.github.io/posts/2024/network-cables-and-connectors/</guid>
      <description>&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Networking_cable&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;img src=&#34;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/6f/Apple_Ethernet_Symbol.svg/1280px-Apple_Ethernet_Symbol.svg.png&#34; alt=&#34;Icon&#34; style=&#34;width:50px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;overview-of-most-commonly-used-networking-cables-and-connectors&#34;&gt;Overview of most commonly used Networking Cables, and Connectors&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In the modern era of computing, various ports, cables, and connectors are utilized to connect peripherals, transfer data, and facilitate communication between devices. Understanding these components is essential for effectively interfacing different hardware components. Below is an overview of some commonly used Networking cables, and connectors:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;!-- # USB (Universal Serial Bus): --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!--    - **Functionality**: USB ports are ubiquitous in modern computing devices, facilitating various connections such as data transfer, charging, and peripheral connectivity. USB Type-C, in particular, offers high-speed data transfer, power delivery, and video output capabilities. --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- &lt;br&gt; --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- The main types of USB connectors are: --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- 1. **USB Type A**: The most common USB connector, found on the host side (e.g. computers, hubs) to connect peripheral devices. --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- 2. **USB Type B**: Used on peripheral devices like printers, scanners, and external hard drives to connect to the host. --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- 3. **USB Type C**: The newest and most versatile USB connector, which can be used on both host and peripheral devices. It is reversible and supports advanced features like USB Power Delivery. --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- In addition, there are also Mini USB and Micro USB connectors, which are smaller versions used primarily on mobile devices. The different USB connector types are not interchangeable, as they have different physical designs and support different USB versions and capabilities. It is important to use the correct connector type for a given device to ensure proper connectivity and functionality. --&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://pauliusuk.github.io/images/Cables/usb.webp&#34; alt=&#34;USB Type A &amp;amp; B&#34; style=&#34;width:400px; display: block; margin: 0 auto;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;imageDetails&#34; style=&#34;margin: 10px 0px 5px 0px; font-size: 19px; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;p class=&#34;imageName&#34;&gt;USB Type A &amp;amp; B&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Common Network Ports</title>
      <link>https://pauliusuk.github.io/posts/2024/common-network-ports/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Apr 2024 02:27:31 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://pauliusuk.github.io/posts/2024/common-network-ports/</guid>
      <description>&lt;a href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_TCP_and_UDP_port_numbers&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;img src=&#34;https://pauliusuk.github.io/images/Network/Binary.webp&#34; alt=&#34;Icon&#34; style=&#34;width:50px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;network-ports-and-protocols&#34;&gt;Network Ports and Protocols&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Ports are crucial endpoints in network communication, facilitating the transfer of data between devices. They allow different services and applications to operate concurrently on a network device by assigning specific numbers to each service. This organization ensures accurate routing of data packets based on predefined protocols. Ports enable essential network functions like web browsing, email, and remote access, making them vital for effective network management and troubleshooting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
